==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Mania
<hw>Ma"ni*a</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>mania</ets>,
Gr. <?/, fr. <?/ to rage; cf. OE. <ets>manie</ets>, F. <ets>manie</ets>.
Cf. <er>Mind</er>, <pos>n.</pos>, <ets>Necromancy</ets>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>Violent derangement of mind; madness; insanity. Cf.
<er>Delirium</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Excessive or unreasonable desire; insane passion
affecting one or many people; <as>as, the tulip
<ex>mania</ex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Mania a potu</b></col> <ety>[L.]</ety>, <cd>madness from
drinking; delirium tremens.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Insanity; derangement; madness; lunacy;
alienation; aberration; delirium; frenzy. See
<er>Insanity</er>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Maniable</ent>⟦br⟧
